---
title: Seven Grain Chiles Rellenos With Avocado Salsa and Zesty Crema
description: This is one tasty way to get stuffed. Really: the poblano peppers in this recipe are filled to the brim with a savory and satisfying mix of tomato, spices, and whole grains. Before they go in the oven, they also get a sprinkle of Monterey Jack (because everything is better with cheese). And when they come out, a few spoonfuls of avocado salsa and zesty crema are added on to keep things fresh and feisty,
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/seven-grain-chiles-rellenos-5bb9c3a9.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/seven-grain-chiles-rellenos-5b9173c1ae08b57baa7ab802-26dc55ea.pdf
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: Mexican
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 670 kcal
  fat: 39 g
  saturated fat: 13 g
  carbohydrates: 72 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 17 g
  fiber: 15 g
  sodium: 560 mg
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/seven-grain-chiles-rellenos-5b9173c1ae08b57baa7ab802
time required: 30 minutes
---

Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Halve @Poblano Pepper{2} lengthwise and remove cores. Rub each with a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{2%teaspoon} and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Place on a #baking sheet{} and roast in oven until soft, about ~{15%minutes}.

Halve, peel, and chop @Yellow Onion{1}(peeled and chopped). Halve @Roma Tomato{1}, then cut into small cubes. Zest @Lime{1}, then halve; cut one half into wedges. Finely mince @Chili Pepper{1}, removing ribs and seeds for less heat. In a #small bowl{}, stir together @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon}, zest, and 1 TBSP water. Season with salt and pepper. Set aside.

Heat a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.

> We recommend a nonstick, ovenproof pan if you have one.

Add onion and cook, tossing occasionally, until just softened, about ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, half the tomato, salt, and pepper to pan with onion. Cook, tossing occasionally, until tomato softens, about ~{2-3%minutes}. Massage @Precooked Seven Whole Grains Rice{8.5%ounce} packet to break up any clumps, then add grains to pan along with ½ cup water. Simmer, stirring every now and then, until warmed through and water is mostly absorbed, about ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon}, then season with salt and pepper. Remove from heat.

Once poblanos are done roasting, stuff each with as much of the grain mixture as will fit. Place in pan with remaining grain mixture, nestling each poblano half in the grains. Sprinkle evenly with @Monterey Jack Cheese{1/2%cup}. Transfer pan to oven. Bake until cheese melts and is slightly crisp, about ~{7-8%minutes}.

> If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer mixture to a small baking dish and arrange stuffed poblanos in there.

Meanwhile, halve, peel, and pit @Avocado{1}, then cut into small cubes. Place in a #medium bowl{} with remaining tomato and juice from lime half. Season with salt and pepper. Toss to combine. Divide stuffed poblanos and grain mixture between plates. Top with avocado salsa. Top with crema and chili (if desired). Serve with lime wedges.